at energy, Medea taken precious treasure king, son heir, Absyrtus. delay pursuit, Medea slew little brother, cut body pieces, dropped side vessel. Thus cruel daughter effected escape. =Achelous= (Acheloʹ) river god, rival Hercules love Deianira. decide bride, Hercules Achelous recourse wrestling bout, fame extends intervening centuries. fierce struggle, Achelous changed form bull rushed upon antagonist lowered horns, intending hurl aside. Hercules eluded onset, seizing huge horns, held firmly broken furious efforts Achelous free . defeated, finally turned river, since known name. =Acheron= (Achʹeron) (see "Youth'Classical Dictionary"). current river Acheron, across souls pass hear decree Pluto, swift boldest swimmer dare attempt breast ; , since bridge, spirits obliged rely upon aid Charon, aged boatman, plied boat available. allow soul enter leaky craft received obolus, fare, ancients carefully placed tongue dead, might delayed passage Pluto. fare forced wait hundred years, Charon reluctantly ferried without charge. "Infernal rivers disgorge burning lake baleful streams ... Sad Acheron, sorrow black deep." Milton. =Achilles= (Achilʹles) valiant Greek heroes Trojan War. son Peleus, King Thessaly. mother, Thetis, plunged , infant, Stygian pool, made invulnerable wherever waters washed ; heel held wetted, part remained vulnerable. shot arrow heel Paris, siege Troy, died wound. =Acidalia= (Acidaʹlia), name given Venus, fountain Boeotia. =Acis= (ʹcis). Sicilian shepherd, loved nymph Galatea. Cyclops jealous crushed hurling rock . Galatea turned blood river--Acis foot Mount Etna. =Actaeon= (Actaeʹ) son Aristaeus, famous huntsman. intruded Diana bathing, changed deer, form hunted dogs torn pieces. =Ades= (ʹdes), see Hades. =Adonis= (Adoʹnis), beautiful attendant Venus, held train. killed boar, turned Venus anemone. "Even sun purple-colored face ta'en last leave weeping morn. Rose-cheeked Adonis hied chase; Hunting loved, love laughed scorn." Shakespeare. =Adrastaea= (Adrastaeʹ), another name Nemesis, goddesses justice. =Adscriptitii Dii= (Adscriptiʹtii Dii) gods second grade. =Adversity=, see Echidna. =Aeacus= (Aeʹacus), judges hell, Minos Rhadamanthus. See Eacus. =Aecastor= (Aecasʹtor), oath used women, referring Temple Castor. =Aedepol= (Aedʹepol), oath used men women, referring Temple Pollux. =Aeetes= (Aeeʹtes), king Colchis, father Medea. =Aegeon= (Aegeʹ), giant fifty heads hundred hands, imprisoned Jupiter Mount Etna. See Briareus. =Aegis= (Aeʹgis), shield Jupiter, called made goat-skin. "thine Aegis Pallas appall'd?" Byron. "Tremendous, Gorgon frowned upon field, circling terrors filled expressive shield." "Full crest Gorgon'head place, eyes roll death, distorted face." Pope. =Aegle= (Aeʹgle). fairest Naiads. =Aello= (Aelʹlo), name Harpies. =Aeneas= (Aeneʹ) son Anchises Venus. great captains escaped destruction Troy. behaved great valor siege, encountering Diomed, even Achilles . Grecians set city fire Aeneas took aged father, Anchises, shoulders, son, Ascanius, wife Creusa, clung garments. saved flames. wandering several years, encountering numerous difficulties, length arrived Italy, hospitably received Latinus, king Latins. death Latinus Aeneas became king. "back, rather burthen, showed stooped load; Aeneas bore sire Upon shoulders fire, knight bear less pack buttocks back." Butler. =Aeolus= (Aeoʹlus) god winds. Jupiter reputed father, mother said daughter Hippotus. Aeolus represented power holding winds confined cavern, occasionally giving liberty blow world. much command supposed Ulysses visited return Troy gave , tied bag, winds prevent voyage prosperous. companions Ulysses, fancying bag contained treasure, cut open came sight Ithaca, port making , contrary winds rushing drove back ship many leagues. residence Aeolus Strongyle, called Strombolo. "Aeolus airy throne power imperial curbs struggling winds, sounding tempests dark prisons binds." Dryden. =Aesculapius= (Aesculaʹpius), god physic, son Apollo. physician Argonauts famous expedition Colchis. became noted cures Pluto became jealous , requested Jupiter kill thunderbolt. revenge son'death Apollo slew Cyclops forged thunderbolt. marriage Epione sons, Machaon Podalirius, famous physicians, daughters, Hygeia, goddess health, renowned. Many temples erected honor Aesculapius, votive tablets hung therein people healed ; famous shrine Epidaurus, , every years, games held honor. god variously represented, famous statue shows seated throne gold ivory. head crowned rays, wears long beard. knotty stick hand, staff entwined serpent , dog lies feet. "Thou dost Aesculapius deride, o'er gallipots triumph ride." Fenton. =Aeson= (Aeʹson) father Jason, restored youth Medea. =Agamemnon= (Agamemʹnon) son Plisthenes brother Menelaus. king Argives. brother'wife famous Helen, daughter Tyndarus, king Sparta; eloped Paris, Agamemnon appointed leader Greeks expedition Troy. =Aganippides= (Aganipʹpides), name Muses, derived fountain Aganippe. =Agineus= (Agineʹ), see Apollo. =Aglaia= (Aglaʹia) Graces. =Agni= (Agʹni). Hindoo god lightning. =Ajax= (ʹjax) bravest Greek warriors Trojan War. father Telamon, mother Eriboea. writers say killed Ulysses; others aver slain Paris; others assert went mad defeated Ulysses, killed . Another Ajax, son Oileus, also took prominent part Trojan War. =Alcestis= (Alcesʹtis), wife Admetus, , save husband'life, died stead, restored life Hercules. =Alcides= (Alciʹdes), names Hercules. =Alcmena= (Alcmeʹna), mother Hercules, daughter Electryon, king Argos. =Alecto= (Alecʹ) Furies. depicted serpents instead hair head, supposed breed pestilence wherever went. =Alectryon= (Alecʹtryon), servant Mars, changed cock warn master rising sun. =Alfadur= (Alʹfadur), Scandinavian Mythology Supreme --Father . =Alma Mammosa= (Alʹma Mammoʹsa), name Ceres. =Alpheus= (Alpheʹ), river god. See Arethusa. =Altar.= structure sacrifice offered. earliest altars merely heaps earth turf rough unhewn stone; mode sacrificing became ceremonious grander altars built. marble brass, ornamented carvings bas-reliefs, corners models heads animals. varied height feet twenty, built solid; others made hollow retain blood victims. provided kind dish, frankincense thrown overpower smell burning fat. probably origin custom burning incense altar. =Amalthaea= (Amalʹthaeʹ), goat nourished Jupiter. =Amazons= (ʹazons) nation women-soldiers lived Scythia. Hercules totally defeated , gave Hippolyte, queen, Theseus wife. race seems exterminated battle. [Illustration: Amazon _See page 20_] =Ambarvalia= (Ambarvaʹlia) festivals honor Ceres, instituted Roman husbandmen purge fields. spring festival head family led animal, usually pig ram, decked oak boughs, round grounds, offered milk new wine. harvest another festival, Ceres presented first-fruits season. See Ceres. =Amber=, see Heliades. =Ambrosia= (Ambroʹsia) Bacchanalian festivals. =Amica= (Amiʹca), name Venus. =Amphion= (Amphiʹ) son Jupiter Antiope. greatly skilled music; said , sound lute, stones arranged regularly make walls city Thebes. "Amphion, , story goes, call Obedient stones make Theban wall." Horace. "New walls Thebes, Amphion thus began." William King. "strains sing Amphion played, list'ning flocks powerful call obeyed." Elphinston. =Amphitrite= (Amphitriʹte) (=Salatia=), wife Neptune, daughter Oceanus Tethys. mother Triton, sea god. "weary chariot sought bowers Amphitrite tending nymphs." Thomson. =Amycus= (Amyʹcus) king Bebrycia. son Neptune, killed Pollux. =Ancaeus= (Ancaeʹ). son Neptune, left cup wine hunt wild boar killed , wine untasted. origin proverb--"'many slip 'twixt cup lip." =Ancilia= (Ancilʹia), twelve sacred shields. first Ancile supposed fallen heaven answer prayer Numa Pompilius. kept greatest care, prophesied fate Roman people depend upon preservation. order priesthood established take care Ancilia, 1st March year shields carried procession, evening great feast, called Coena Saliaris. =Andromeda= (Andromʹeda), daughter Cepheus, king Ethiopians, wife Perseus, rescued chained rock devoured sea-monster. =Anemone= (Anemʹ). Venus changed Adonis flower. =Angeronia= (Angeroʹnia), otherwise Volupia, goddess power dispelling anguish mind. =Anna Perenna= (Anna Perenʹna), rural divinities. =Antaeus= (Antaeʹ), giant vanquished Hercules. time Hercules threw giant gained fresh strength touching earth, Hercules lifted ground squeezed death. =Anteros= (ʹteros), Cupids, sons Venus. =Anticlea= (Anticʹlea), mother Ulysses. =Antiope= (Antiʹope) wife Lycus, King Thebes. Jupiter, disguised satyr, led astray corrupted . =Anubis= (Anuʹbis) (Hermanubis (Hermanʹubis)). "god half dog, dog half man." Called _Barker_ Virgil poets. =Aonides= (Aonʹides), name Muses, country Aonia. =Apaturia= (Apaturʹia), Athenian festival, received name Greek word signifying deceit. =Aphrodite= (Aphʹrodiʹte), Greek name Venus. =Apis=, name given Jupiter inhabitants Lower Nile. Also miraculous ox, worshiped Egypt. =Apis= (ʹpis), King Argivia. Afterward called Serapis, greatest god Egyptians. =Apollo= (Apolʹlo). famous god, time King Arcadia, son Jupiter Latona. known several names, principally following:--Sol (sun); Cynthius, mountain called Cynthus Isle Delos, island native place obtained name Delius; Delphinius, occasionally assuming shape dolphin. name Delphicus derived connection splendid Temple Delphi, uttered famous oracles. writers record oracle became dumb Jesus Christ born. common names Apollo Didymaeus, Nomius, Paean, Phoebus. Greeks called Agineus, streets guardianship, called Pythius killed serpent Python. Apollo usually represented handsome young man without beard, crowned laurel, hand bow, lyre. favorite residence Apollo Mount Parnassus, mountain Phocis, Greece, presided Muses. Apollo accredited father several children, renowned Aesculapius Phaeton. "Wilt thou music? Hark! Apollo plays. twenty cagëd nightingales sing." Shakespeare. =Apotheosis= (Apotheʹosis). consecration god. ceremony deification. =Arachne= (Arachʹne), Lydian princess, challenged Minerva spinning contest, Minerva struck head spindle, turned spider. "... disemboweled web, Arachne, hall kitchen spreads. Obvious vagrant flies." John Phillips. =Arcadia= (Arcaʹdia), delightful country center Peloponnessus, favorite place gods. Apollo reputed King Arcadia. =Arcas= (Arʹcas), son Calisto, turned -bear; afterward constellation called Ursa Minor. =Archer=, see Chiron. =Areopagitae= (Areopʹagiʹtae), judges sat Areopagus. =Areopagus= (Areopʹagus), hill Athens Mars tried murder twelve gods. =Ares= (ʹres). Mars, god war. =Arethusa= (Arethuʹsa) nymphs Diana. fled Alpheus, river god, enabled escape turned Diana rivulet ran underground. virtuous beautiful. =Argonauts= (Arʹgonauts). name given fifty heroes sailed Colchis ship Argo, command Jason, fetch Golden Fleece. =Argus= (Arʹgus) god hundred eyes slept watched turns. charged Juno watch Io, , slain Mercury, changed Juno peacock. =Ariadne= (Ariadʹne), daughter Minos, King Crete. enabling Theseus get Labyrinth means clew thread, fled Naxos, ungratefully deserted ; Bacchus wooed married , crown stars gave turned constellation. =Arion= (Ariʹ) famous lyric poet Methymna, Island Lesbos, gained great riches art. pretty fable made name Arion famous. traveling Lesbos companions robbed , proposed throw sea. entreated seamen play upon harp threw overboard, played sweetly dolphins flocked round vessel. threw sea, dolphins took carried Taenarus, near Corinth. act dolphin raised heaven constellation. =Aristaeus= (Aristaeʹ), son Apollo Cyrene, god trees; also taught mankind use honey, get oil olives. celebrated hunter. famous son Actaeon. =Armata= (Armaʹta), names Venus, given Spartan women. =Artemis= (Arʹtemis). Grecian name Diana, festivals Delphi called Artemisia. =Arts Sciences=, see Muses. =Aruspices= (Arusʹpices), sacrificial priests. =Ascalaphus= (Ascalʹaphus) changed owl, harbinger misfortune, Ceres, informed Pluto Proserpine partaken food infernal regions, thus prevented return earth. =Ascanius= (Ascaʹnius), son Aeneas Creusa. =Ascolia= (Ascolʹia), Bacchanalian feasts, Greek word meaning leather bottle. bottles used games jump . =Asopus= (Asoʹpus). son Jupiter, killed father'thunderbolts. =Assabinus= (Assabiʹnus), Ethiopian name Jupiter. =Ass'ears=, see Midas. =Astarte= (Astarʹte), Eastern names Venus. =Asteria= (Asteʹria), daughter Caeus, carried away Jupiter, assumed shape eagle. =Astrea= (Astreʹ), mother Nemesis, goddess justice; returned heaven earth became corrupt. "... Chaste Astrea fled, sought protection native sky." John Hughes. =Atalanta= (Atalanʹta) daughter Caeneus. oracle told marriage fatal , , beautiful, many suitors. swift runner, , get rid admirers, promised marry outstrip race, defeated slain. Hippomenes, however, aid Venus, successful. goddess gave golden apples, dropped whenever Atalanta caught race. stopped pick , victorious married . afterward turned lions Cybele, profaning temple. =Ate= (ʹte). goddess revenge, also called goddess discord evil. banished heaven father Jupiter. "Ate side come hot hell." Shakespeare. =Athena= (Atheʹna), name obtained Minerva tutelary goddess Athens. =Atlas=, King Mauritania, Morocco, Africa. also great astronomer. depicted globe back, name signifying great toil labor. inhospitality Perseus king changed mountain bears name Atlas. chain mountains Africa called , Atlantic Ocean. daughters wife Pleione, called common name, Pleiades; wife Aethra , , manner, called Hyades. Pleiades Hyades celestial constellations. =Atreus= (ʹreus), type fraternal hatred. dislike brother Thyestes went extent killing roasting nephews, inviting father feast, Thyestes thought sign reconciliation, victim brother'detestable cruelty. "Media must draw murdering knife, Atreus horrid feast prepare." Lord Roscommon. =Atropos= (ʹropos), sisters called Fates, held shears ready cut thread life. =Atys= (ʹtys), son Croesus, born dumb, fight saw soldier kill king gained speech, cried , "Save king!" string held tongue broken. =Atys= (ʹtys) youth beloved Aurora, slain father, , according Ovid, afterward turned pine-tree. =Augaeas= (Augʹaeas), king Elis, owner stable Hercules cleansed thousand oxen kept thirty years. cleansed turning river Alpheus . Augaeas promised give Hercules tenth part cattle trouble , neglecting keep promise, Hercules slew . =Augury= (Auʹgury). means adopted Romans forming judgment futurity flight birds, officiating priest called augur. =Aurora= (Auroʹra), goddess morning, "Whose rosy fingers ope gates day." daughter Sol, sun, mother stars winds. represented riding splendid golden chariot drawn white horses. goddess loved Tithonus, begged gods grant immortality, forgot ask time get old decrepit. See Tithonus. "... soon -cheering sun , farthest east, begin draw shady curtains Aurora'bed." Shakespeare. =Auster= (Ausʹter), south wind, son Jupiter. =Avernus= (Averʹnus), poisonous lake, referred poets entrance infernal regions, really lake Campania, Italy. =Averruncus Deus= (Averrunʹcus Deus), Roman god, divert people evil-. =Axe=, see Daedalus. =Baal= (Baʹal), god Phoenicians. =Baal-Peor= (Baʹal-Peʹ), Moabitish god, associated licentiousness obscenity. modern name Belphegor. =Babes=, see Rumia Dea. =Bacchantes= (Bacʹchantes). priestesses Bacchus. =Bacchus= (Bacʹchus), god wine, son Jupiter Semele. said married Ariadne, daughter Minos, King Crete, deserted Theseus. distinguished children Hymen, god marriage. Bacchus sometimes referred names Dionysius, Biformis, Brisaeus, Iacchus, Lenaeus, Lyceus, Liber, Liber Pater, symbol liberty. god wine usually represented crowned vine ivy leaves. left hand thyrsus, kind javelin, fir cone head, encircled ivy vine. chariot drawn lions, tigers, panthers. "Jolly Bacchus, god pleasure, Charmed world drink dances." . Parnell, 1700. =Balios= (Baʹlios). famous horse given Neptune Peleus wedding present, afterward given Achilles. =Barker=, see Anubis. =Bassarides= (Bassarʹides). priestesses Bacchus sometimes called. =Battle=, see Valhalla. =Bear=, see Calisto. =Beauty=, see Venus. =Bees=, see Mellona. =Belisama= (Belisaʹma), goddess Gauls. name means Queen Heaven. =Bellerophon= (Bellerʹophon), hero destroyed monster called Chimaera. =Bellona= (Belloʹna), goddess war, wife Mars. 24th March called Bellona'Day, votaries cut knives drank blood sacrifice. "Dirae'Discord'steps Bellona treads, shakes iron rod heads." =Belphegor= (Belpheʹgor), see Baal-Peor. =Belus= (ʹlus). Chaldean name sun. =Berecynthia= (Berecynʹthia), name Cybele, mountain worshiped. =Biformis= (Biʹformis), name Bacchus, accounted bearded beardless. =Birds=, see Augury. =Births=, see Lucina Levana. =Blacksmith=, see Brontes Vulcan. =Blind=, see Thamyris. =Blue eyes=, see Glaukopis. =Bona Dea= (Boʹna Deʹ). "bountiful goddess," whose festival celebrated Romans much magnificence. See Ceres. =Bonus Eventus= (Boʹnus Evenʹtus). god good success, rural divinity. =Boreas= (Boʹreas), north wind, son Astraeus Aurora. "... snatched rigid north, native bed, bleak Boreas blew, bore nearer sun...." Young, 1710. =Boundaries=, see Terminus. =Boxing=, see Pollux. =Brahma= (Brahʹma). great Indian deity, represented heads looking quarters globe. =Briareus= (Briʹareus), famous giant. See Aegeon. =Brisaeus= (Brisʹaeus). name Bacchus, referring use grapes honey. =Brontes= (Brontʹes), Cyclops. personification blacksmith. =Bubona= (Buboʹna), goddess herdsmen, rural divinities. =Buddha= (Budʹdha). Primitively, pagan deity, Vishnu Hindoos. =Byblis= (Bybʹlis). niece Sol, mentioned Ovid. shed many tears unrequited love turned fountain. "Thus Phoebeian Byblis, spent tears, Becomes living fountain, yet bears name." Ovid. =Cabiri= (Cabʹiri). mysterious rites connected worship deities obscene writers refer secrets unlawful reveal. =Cacodaemon= (Cacʹodaeʹmon). Greek name evil spirit. =Cacus= (Caʹcus), -headed monster robber. =Cadmus= (Cadʹmus), earliest Greek demi-gods. reputed inventor letters, alphabet consisted sixteen letters. Cadmus slew Boeotian dragon, sowed teeth ground, sprang armed man. =Caduceus= (Caduʹceus). rod carried Mercury. winged serpents entwined round top end. supposed possess power producing sleep, Milton refers _Paradise Lost_ "opiate rod." =Calisto= (Calisʹ), Arcadian nymph, turned -bear Jupiter. form hunted son Arcas, killed Jupiter turned -bear. nymph son form constellations known Great Bear Little Bear. =Calliope= (Calliʹope). Muse presided epic poetry rhetoric. generally depicted using stylus wax tablets, ancient writing materials. =Calpe= (Calʹpe). pillars Hercules. =Calypso= (Calypʹ) queen island Ogygia, Ulysses wrecked, persuaded remain years. =Cama= (Caʹma). Indian god love marriage. =Camillus= (Camilʹlus), name Mercury, office minister gods. =Canache= (ʹache). name Actaeon'hounds. =Canopus= (Canoʹpus). Egyptian god water, conqueror fire. =Capis= (Capʹ) =Capula= (Capʹula). peculiar cup ears, used drinking health deities. =Capitolinus= (Capitoliʹnus). name Jupiter, Capitoline hill, top temple built dedicated . =Capripedes= (Capʹriʹpedes). Pan, Egipans, Satyrs, Fauns, called goat'feet. =Caprotina= (Caprotiʹna). name Juno. =Cassandra= (Cassanʹdra), daughter Priam Hecuba, granted Apollo power seeing futurity, offended god prevented people believing predictions. =Cassiopeia= (Cassiopeʹia). Ethiopian queen set beauty comparison Nereides, thereupon chained rock left devoured sea-monster, delivered Perseus. See Andromeda. =Castalia= (Castaʹlia). fountains Mount Parnassus, sacred Muses. =Castalides= (Castaʹliʹdes), name Muses, fountain Castalia Castalius. =Castor= (Casʹtor), son Jupiter Leda, twin brother Pollux, noted skill horsemanship. went Jason quest Golden Fleece. =Cauther= (Cauʹther), Mohammedan mythology, lake paradise, whose waters sweet honey, cold snow, clear crystal; believer tastes thereof said thirst . =Celeno= (Celʹeno) Harpies, progenitor Zephyrus, west wind. =Centaur= (Cenʹtaur). huntsman forepart like man, remainder body like horse. Centauri lived Thessaly. =Cephalus= (Cepʹhalus) married Procris, accidentally slew shooting secretly watching , thinking wild beast. Cephalus type constancy. =Ceraunius= (Cerauʹnius). Greek name Jupiter, meaning Fulminator, thunderbolts. =Cerberus= (Cerʹberus). Pluto'famous -headed dog, guarded gate infernal regions, preventing living entering, inhabitants going . "-headed Cerberus, fate Posted Pluto'iron gate; Low crouching rolls haggard eyes, Ecstatic, foregoes prize." =Ceremonies=, see Themis. [Illustration: Apollo Belvedere _See page 23_] =Ceres= (Ceʹres), daughter Saturn, goddess agriculture, fruits earth. taught Triptolemus grow corn, sent teach inhabitants earth. known names Magna Dea, Bona Dea, Alma Mammosa, Thesmorphonis. Ceres mother Proserpine. See Ambarvalia. "Ceres bland, annual rites paid green turf beneath fragrant shade.-- ... hinds bend low Ceres' shrine, Mix honey sweet milk mellow wine, Thrice lead victim new fruits around, Ceres call, choral hymns resound." "Ceres first furrows plowed, gave sweet fruits every good allowed." Pope. =Cestus= (Cesʹtus), girdle Venus, excited irresistible affection. =Chaos= (Chaʹos) allegorically represented confused mass matter supposed existed creation world, world formed. "... Behold throne Chaos, dark pavilion spread Wide wasteful deep; enthroned Sat sable-vested Night, eldest things, consort reign." Milton. =Charon= (Charʹ) son Nox Erebus. ferryman conveyed spirits dead, boat, rivers Acheron Styx Elysian Fields. "Charon'toll" coin put hands dead pay grim ferryman. "dark mansions dead, Charon lazy boat Ferries o'er Lethe'sedgy moat." =Charybdis= (Charybʹdis). dangerous whirlpool coast Sicily. Personified, supposed woman plundered travelers, last killed Hercules. Scylla Charybdis generally spoken together represent alternative dangers. "Charybdis barks, Polyphemus roars." Francis. =Chemos= (Cheʹmos). Moabitish god war. =Children=, see Nundina. =Chimaera= (Chimaeʹra). wild illusion, personified monster slain Bellerophon. head breast lion, body goat, tail serpent. used vomit fire. "... craggy top Chimera dwells, lion'face mane, goat'rough body serpent'train." Pope. "First, dire Chimera'conquest enjoined, mingled monster mortal kind. Behind, dragon'fiery tail spread, goat'rough body bore lion'head, pitchy nostrils flaky flames expire, gaping throat emits infernal fire." Milton. =Chiron= (Chiʹron), centaur taught Achilles hunting, music, use medicinal herbs. Jupiter placed among stars, appears Sagittarius, Archer. =Chloris= (Chloʹris). Greek name Flora, goddess flowers. =Chou.= Egyptian god corresponding Roman Hercules. =Chronos= (Chroʹnos). Time, Grecian name Saturn. =Cillaros= (Cilʹlaros), see Cyllaros. =Circe= (Cirʹce), daughter Sun. knowledge poisonous herbs enabled destroy husband, King Sarmatians, act banished. Ulysses landed Aeaea, lived, turned followers swine. =Cisseta= (Cisseʹta). name Actaeon'hounds. =Citherides= (Citherʹides). name Muses, Mount Citheron. =Clio= (Cliʹo). Muses, daughter Jupiter Mnemosyne. presided history. =Cloacina= (Cloaciʹna). Roman goddess sewers. =Clotho= (Cloʹtho) Fates. present births, held distaff spun thread life. See Atropos Lachesis. =Clowns Lycia, = (Lyʹcia), changed frogs Latona, refused allow drink streamlets. =Cluacina= (Cluʹaciʹna). name Venus, given time reconciliation Romans Sabines, ratified near statue goddess. =Clytemnestra= (Clyʹtemnesʹtra), wife Agamemnon, slew husband married Aegisthus. attempted kill son Orestes, delivered sister Electra, sent away Strophius. afterward returned slew Clytemnestra Aegisthus. =Clytie= (Clytʹie). nymph got changed sunflower love Apollo unrequited. form flower still supposed turning toward Sol, name Apollo. =Cneph.= Egyptian mythology creator universe. =Cocytus= (Cocyʹtus), river Lamentation. rivers infernal regions. "Infernal rivers disgorge burning lake baleful streams. ... Cocytus, named lamentation loud. Heard rueful stream." Milton. =Coeculus= (Coeʹculus), violent robber, son Vulcan. =Coelus= (Coeʹlus), also called Uranus (Heaven), ancient gods. =Coena Saliaris= (Coeʹna Saliaʹris), see Ancilia. =C