se Latona , towered Cybele, Mother hundred gods, Juno dares give odds." Milton. =Cyclops= (Cyʹclops) =Cyclopes= (Cyʹclopes) gigantic, -eyed workmen Vulcan, made Jove'thunderbolts. Hesiod gives names Arges, Brontes, Steropes. "Meantime, Cyclop raging wound, Spreads wide arms, searches round round." Pope. =Cygnus= (Cygʹnus), bosom friend Phaeton. died grief death friend, turned swan. =Cyllaros= (Cyllʹaros), Castor'horses. color mentioned coal-black, white legs tail. See Cillaros. =Cyllo= (Cylʹlo). name Actaeon'hounds, lame. =Cyllopotes= (Cyllopʹotes). name given Actaeon'hounds limped. =Cynosure= (Cynʹosure). nurses Jupiter, turned god conspicuous constellation. "Towers battlements sees Bosomed high tufted trees, perhaps beauty lies, Cynosure neighboring eyes." Milton. =Cyparissus= (Cyparisʹsus). boy Apollo fond; died changed, Apollo'intercession, cypress tree, branches typify mourning. =Cypress= (Cyʹpress), see Cyparissus. =Cypria= (Cyʹpria). name Venus, worshiped island Cyprus. =Cythera= (Cythʹera). name Venus, island wafted shell. =Dactyli= (Dactyʹli) priests Cybele. given name, , like fingers, number. =Daedalus= (Daedʹalus) great architect sculptor. invented wedge, axe, level, gimlet, first use sails. Daedalus also constructed famous labyrinth Minos, King Crete. See Icarus. "Daedalus, behold, fate assigned, task proportioned thy mighty mind." Pope. =Dagon= (Daʹgon). god Philistines, half man half fish, like mermaid. Milton describes "Upward man downward fish." =Dahak= (Daʹhak). Persian devil. =Daityas= (Daiʹtyas). Hindoo mythology devils evil gods. =Danae= (Danʹae) daughter Acrisius Eurydice. son Jupiter, drifted sea boat, saved Polydectes educated. [Illustration: Fountain Cybele (Rhea) _See page 42_] =Danaides= (Danaʹides), see Danaus. =Danaus= (Danaʹ), King Argos, father fifty daughters, , , command father, slew husbands directly marriage. crime condemned task forever trying draw water vessels without bottoms. See Hypermnestra. =Dancing=, see Terpsichore. =Dangers=, see Charybdis, also Scylla. =Daphne= (Daphʹne). goddess earth. Apollo courted , fled , , request, turned laurel tree. "... Daphne Root-bound, fled Apollo." Milton. =Dardanus= (Darʹdanus), son Jupiter, built city Dardania, writers accounted founder Troy. =Dead-toll=, see Charon. =Death=, see Nox. =Deceiver, =, see Apaturia. =Deianira= (Deianiʹra), daughter Oeneus, wife Hercules. See Hercules. =Delius= (Deʹlius), name Apollo, island born. =Delphi= (Delʹphi). town Mount Parnassus, famous oracle, temple Apollo. See Delphos. =Delphicus= (Delʹphicus). name Apollo, Delphi. =Delphos= (Delʹphos), place temple built, oracle Apollo given. =Demarus= (Deʹmarus). Phoenician name Jupiter. =Demogorgon= (Deʹmogorʹgon) tyrant genius soil earth, life support plants. depicted old man covered moss, said live underground. sometimes called king elves fays. "wast begot Demogorgon'hall saw'st secrets world unmade." Spenser. =Deucalion= (Deucaʹlion), demi-gods, son Prometheus Pyrra. wife, making ship, survived deluge Jupiter sent earth, circa 1503 B.C. =Devil=, see Dahak, Daityas, Obambou. =Diana= (Diʹana), goddess hunting chastity. sister Apollo, daughter Jupiter Latona. known among Greeks Diana Phoebe, honored triform goddess. celestial divinity called Luna; terrestrial Diana Dictynna; infernal regions Hecate. =Dictynna= (Dictynʹna), Greek name Diana terrestrial goddess. =Dido= (Diʹ). daughter Belus, King Tyre. princess bought piece land Africa large encompassed bullock'hide, purchase completed, cut hide strips, secured large tract land. built Carthage; Virgil tells Aeneas shipwrecked neighboring coast received every kindness, last fell love . Aeneas reciprocate affections, grieved stabbed . tale told _Facetiae Cantabrigienses_ Professor Porson, set party, conversation turned subject punning, Porson observing pun subject, person present defied Latin gerunds, _di_, __, _dum_, , however, immediately following admirable couplet: "Dido found Aeneas come, mourned silence, _Dido dumb_." =Dies Pater= (Diʹes Paʹter), Father Day, name Jupiter. =Dii Selecti= (Dii Selecʹti) composed second class gods. Coelus, Saturn, Genius, Oreus, Sol, Bacchus, Terra, Luna. =Dindymene= (Dinʹdymeʹne). name Cybele, mountain worshiped. "Dindymene, priest possest, sounding cymbals shake breast Like furious anger." Francis. =Diomedes= (Diomeʹdes), cruel tyrant Thrace, fed mares flesh guests. overcome Hercules, given horses food. =Dione= (Dioʹne). poetic name Venus. =Dionysia= (Dionyʹsia) festivals honor Bacchus. =Dionysius= (Dionyʹsius). name Bacchus, either father Jupiter (Dios), nurses, nymphs called Nysae. =Dioscuri= (Diosʹcuri). Castor Pollux, sons Jupiter. =Dirae= (Diʹrae). name Furies. =Dis.= name Pluto, god hell, signifying riches. "... fair field Enna, Proserpine gathering flowers, fairer flower, gloomy Dis gathered." Milton. =Discord=, see Ate. =Discordia= (Discorʹdia), sister Nemesis, Furies, Death, driven heaven sown discord among gods. =Diseases=, see Pandora. =Distaff=, see Pallas. =Dithyrambus.= surname Bacchus. =Dodona= (Dodoʹna) celebrated oracle Jupiter. "O , Dodona, thine aged grove, Prophetic fount, oracle divine?" Byron. =Dodonaeus= (Dodonaeʹ). name Jupiter, city Dodona. =Dog=, see Lares. =Dolabra= (Dolaʹbra). knife used priests cut sacrifices. =Dolphin=, see Arion. =Doorga= (Doorʹga). Hindoo goddess. =Doris= (ʹris) daughter Oceanus, sister Nereus, marine deities. sisters sprang several tribes water nymphs. =Doto= (ʹ). Nereids sea nymphs. =Draco= (Draʹco). Actaeon'hounds. =Dragon=, -headed, see Geryon. =Dreams=, see Morpheus. =Dryads= (Dryʹads) rural deities, nymphs forests, votaries offered oil, milk, honey. "Flushed resistless charms fired love nymph little Dryad grove." Ticknell. =Dumbness= (Dumbʹness), see Atys. =Dweurgar= (Dweurʹgar). Scandinavian god Echo--pigmy. =Eacus= (Eʹacus), son Jupiter Egina, judges infernal regions, appointed judge Europeans. See Aeacus. =Earth=, see Antaeus. =Eblis= (Ebʹlis), Mohammedan evil genius. =Echidna= (Echidʹna). woman