mine jaws, proof steel hides plumes remain strike impenetrable fiends vain." =Harpikruti= (Harpiʹkruti). Egyptian name god Harpocrates. =Harpocrates= (Harpocʹrates), Horus, Egyptian god, son Osiris Isis. god silence secrecy. usually represented young man, holding finger hand lips (expressive command preserve silence), hand holds cornucopia, signifying early vegetation. =Harvest=, see Segetia. Roman divinity, invoked husbandman harvest might plentiful. =Hawk=, see Nysus. =Hazis= (Haʹzis). Syrian war-god. =Health=, see Hygeia Salus. =Heaven=, =Queen =, (Heaʹven) see Belisama. =God =, see Coelus. =Hebe= (ʹ), daughter Zeus (Jupiter) Hera (Juno), goddess youth. cup-bearer Jupiter gods, awkward fall festival, causing alight indecent posture, displeased Jupiter deprived office, Ganymede appointed stead. "Wreathed smiles, hung Hebe'cheek, love live dimples sleek." Milton. "Bright Hebe waits; Hebe ever young whirling wheels chariot hung." Pope. =Hecate= (Hecʹate). goddesses known name, generally referred modern literature Hecate, Proserpine, name Diana known infernal regions. heaven name Luna, terrestrial name Diana. moon-goddess, generally represented art bodies, standing back back, torch, sword, lance right hand. =Hecuba= (Hecʹuba). wife Priam, king Troy, mother Paris. Taken captive Trojan war, fell lot Ulysses destruction Troy, afterwards changed hound. "'Hecuba , Hecuba?" Shakespeare. =Heifer=, see Ino. =Helena= (Helʹena) child beautiful Theseus Perithous stole , restored Castor Pollux. became wife Menelaus, king Sparta, eloped Paris, thus caused Trojan War. death Paris married Deiphobus, brother, betrayed Menelaus. afterward tied tree strangled order Polyxo, king Rhodes. =Heliades, = (ʹliades), daughters Sol, sisters Phaeton, whose death sad stood mourning till became metamorphosed poplar trees, tears turned amber. =Helicon= (Helʹicon). mountain Boeotia sacred Muses, place fountain Hippocrene flowed. "Yet still doting rhymer dreams, sings Helicon'bright streams; Helicon