te= (Ichnobaʹte). Actaeon'hounds; word means tracker. =Idaea= (Idaeʹ). name Cybele, Mount Ida, worshiped. =Idaean Mother= (IdaeʹMother). Cybele sometimes called, Cyprus, grove sacred Venus. =Idalia= (Idaʹlia). name Venus, Mount Idalus, Cyprus, grove sacred Venus. =Imperator= (Imperaʹtor) name Jupiter, given Praeneste. =Inachus= (ʹnachus) earliest demi-gods heroes, King Argos. =Incendiary=, see Erostratus. =Incense=, see Venus. =Incubus= (ʹcubus). Roman name Pan, meaning Nightmare. See Innus. =Indigetes= (Indigʹetes) deified mortals, gods fourth order. peculiar district. =Indra= (ʹdra). Hindoo Jupiter; wife Indrant, presides winds thunder. =Infants=, see Natio. =Innus= (ʹnus). name Pan, Incubus. =Ino= (ʹo), second wife Athamas, King Thebes, father Phryxus Helle. Ino children, ascend throne Phryxus Helle alive. Ino therefore persecuted degree determined escape. ram, whose hide became Golden Fleece (see Phryxus Helle). Ino destroyed , changed Neptune sea-goddess. =Inoa= (Inoʹ) festivals memory Ino. =Instrumental Music=, see Euterpe. =Io= (ʹo) daughter Inachus, priestess Juno Argos. Jupiter courted , detected Juno, god turned Io beautiful heifer. Juno demanded beast Jupiter, set hundred-eyed Argus watch . Jupiter persuaded Mercury destroy Argus, Io set liberty, restored human shape. Juno continued persecutions, Io wander place place till came Egypt, became wife King Osiris, won good opinions Egyptians death worshiped goddess Isis. =Iolaus= (Iolaʹ), son Iphicles, assisted Hercules conquering Hydra, burning hot irons place heads cut ; assistance restored youth Hebe. Lovers used go monument Phocis ratify vows fidelity. =Iothun= (Ioʹthun). Celtic mythological monsters, giants. =Iphicles= (Iphʹicles) twin brother Hercules, father Iolaus. =Iphigenia= (Iphigeniʹ) daughter Agamemnon Clytemnestra. Agamemnon made vow Diana, involved sacrifice Iphigenia, critical moment carried heaven, beautiful goat found altar place. =Iris= (ʹris), daughter Thaumas Electra, attendant Juno, messengers gods. duty cut thread detained expiring souls. personification rainbow. =Iron=, see Vulcan. =Isis= (ʹsis), wife Osiris, much worshiped divinity Egyptians. See Io. =Itys= (ʹtys) killed mother Procne years old, given father Tereus, Thracian Daulis, food. gods enraged turned Itys pheasant, Procne swallow, Tereus hawk. =Ixion= (Ixiʹ), son Phlegyas, King Lapithae. attempting produce thunder, Jupiter cast hell, bound wheel, surrounded serpents, forever turning river fire. "powers vengeance, hear, Touched compassion, drop tear; Ixion'rapid wheel bound, Fixed attention sound." F. Lewis. ", Ixion fix'd, wretch shall feel giddy motion whirling wheel." Pope. =Jani= (Jaʹni) place Rome statues Janus, meeting-place usurers creditors. =Janitor= (Jaʹnitor). title Janus, gates doors private houses called Januae. =Janus= (Jaʹnus). king Italy, said son Coelus, others say Apollo; sheltered Saturn driven heaven Jupiter. Janus presided highways, gates, locks, usually represented faces, acquainted past future; , according others, taken sun, opens day rising, shuts setting. brazen temple erected Rome, always open time war, closed peace. "Old Janus, please, Grave -faced father." "-faced Janus moral find,-- look forward, glance behind." Colman. =Japetus= (Japʹetus), son Coelus Terra, husband Clymene. looked upon Greeks father mankind. See Iapetos. =Jason= (Jaʹson), son Aeson, king Iolcos; brought centaur Chiron. uncle Aeeta sent fetch Golden Fleece Colchis (see Argonauts). went ship Argo forty-companions, flower Greek youth. help Juno got safe Colchis, King Aeetes promised restore Golden Fleece condition Argonauts performed certain services. Jason tame wild fiery bulls, make plow field Mars; sow ground teeth serpent, spring armed men fight plowed field Mars; kill fiery dragon guarded tree Golden Fleece hung. fate Jason rest Argonauts seemed certain; Medea, king'daughter, fell love Jason, help charms gave overcame difficulties king put way. took away Golden Fleece Medea also. king sent 