responding English St. George, still invoked Turks go war. =Kiun= (Kiʹun). Egyptian Venus. =Kneph.= Egyptian god, ram'head man'body. =Krishna= (Krishʹna). Indian god, revenger wrongs; also called Indian Apollo. =Krodo= (Kroʹ). Saxon Saturn. =Kumara= (Kuʹmaʹra). war-god Hindoos. =Kuvera= (Kuʹvera). Hindoo god riches. =Labe= (Laʹ). Arabian Circe, unlimited power metamorphosis. =Labor= (Labʹ), see Atlas, Hercules. =Labyrinth=, see Theseus. =Lachesis= (Lachʹesis). goddesses Fate, Parcae. spun thread life. =Lacinia= (Lacinʹia). name Juno. =Lactura.= goddesses growing corn. =Ladon= (Laʹ). dragon guarded apples garden Hesperides. Also name Actaeon'hounds. Also river Arcadia Syrinx fled pursued Pan, changed reed, Pan made first pipe. =Laelaps= (Laeʹlaps). Diana'hunting-dogs, , pursuing wild boar, petrified. Also name Actaeon'hounds. =Laksmi= (Laksʹmi) Hindoo goddess wealth pleasure. husbands Vishnu. =Lamentation=, see Cocytus. =Lamia= (Lamʹia). evil deity among Greeks Romans, great dread children, credit constantly enticing away destroying. =Lamp=, see Lares Penates. =Lampos= (Lamʹpos). Aurora'chariot horses, Phaeton. =Laocoon= (Laocʹoon). priests Apollo, , sons, strangled death serpents, opposed admission fatal wooden horse Troy. =Laomedon= (Laomʹedon), son Ilus, Trojan king. famous , assistance Apollo Neptune, built walls Troy. =Lapis= (Lapʹ). oath stone. Romans used swear Jupiter Lapis. =Lapithus= (Lapʹithus), son Apollo. numerous children called Lapithae, notorious fight centaurs nuptial feast Perithous Hippodamia. =Lares Penates= (Laʹres Penaʹtes) sons Mercury Lara, , mythologists say, Jupiter Lamida. belonged lower order Roman gods, presided homes families. statues generally fixed within doors houses, near hearths. Lamps sacred , symbols vigilance, dog sacrifice. =Lark=, see Scylla Nysus. =Latona= (Latoʹna), daughter Coelus Phoebe, mother Apollo Diana. admired much Jupiter, Juno jealous, Latona object goddess' constant persecution. =Laughter=, see Momus Venus. =Laurel