d lotus-plant. =Lotus-Plant= (Loʹtus-Plant), see Lotis. =Love=, see Cupid, Eros, Venus. =Lucian= (Luʹcian). impersonation folly, changed ass. =Lucifer= (Luʹcifer). morning star. =Lucina= (Luciʹna). goddess presides birth children. daughter Jupiter Juno, , according others, Latona. "Lucina, hail! named thine grove, light thou giv'st ." Ovid. =Lud.= ancient British mythology king Britons. said given name London. =Luna= (Luʹna). name Diana celestial divinity. See Diana Hecate. Also, Italian goddess moon. =Lupercus= (Luʹpercus), Pan. Roman god fertility; festival day 15th February, festivals called Lupercalia. =Lycaonian Food= (Lycaonʹian). Execrable viands, supplied Jupiter Lycaon. test divine knowledge god served human flesh, Jove discovered, punished Lycaon turning wolf. =Lycian Clowns= turned frogs Latona Ceres. =Lymniades= (Lymniʹades). Nymphs resided marshes. =Lynceus= (Lynʹceus). Argonauts. personification sharpsightedness. =Lyre.= musical instrument constantly associated doings ancient deities. Amphion built walls Thebes music lyre. Arion charmed dolphins similar way. Hercules broke head Linus, music-master, lyre learning use; Orpheus charmed savage beasts, even Harpies gods infernal regions, enchanting music stringed lyre. See Mercury. =Maenades= (Maenʹades). Priestesses Bacchus. =Magicians=, see Telchines. =Magna Dea= (Magʹna Deʹ), name Ceres. =Magpies=, see Pierides. =Mahasoor= (Maʹhaʹsoor). Hindoo god evil. =Maia= (Maʹia). mother Grecian Mercury. =Mammon= (Mamʹmon). money god. =Manes= (Maʹnes). souls departed. Roman god funerals tombs. "Manes, Manes bear. 're cleansed abodes repair, breathe ample fields soft Elysian air." =Manuring Land=, see Picumnus. =March 24=, Bellona'Day. See Bellona. =Marina= (Mariʹna). name Venus, meaning sea-foam, formed froth sea. See Aphrodite. =Marriage=, see Cama, Hymen, Juno, Jugatinus. =Mars=, god war, son Jupiter Juno. Venus favorite goddess, among children Cupid, Anteros, Harmonia. Trojan War Mars took part Trojans, defeated 