nished celestial regions, conspired Pluto dethrone Jupiter. Neptune married Amphitrite, daughter Oceanus Tethys, son named Triton. also father Polyphemus (Cyclopes), Phoreus, Proteus. Neptune represented seated shell chariot, drawn dolphins sea-horses, surrounded Tritons sea-nymphs. holds hand trident, rules waves. Though marine deity, reputed presided horse-training horse-races; principally known god ocean; functions god portrayed sea horses chariot drawn, fore-half animal horse, hind-half dolphin. Ships also protection, whenever appeared ocean dead calm. =Nereides, = (Nereʹides), aquatic nymphs. daughters Nereus Doris, fifty number. generally represented beautiful girls riding dolphins, carrying tridents right hand garlands flowers. =Nereus= (Nereʹ). sea deity, husband Doris. gift prophecy, foretold fates; also power assuming various shapes, enabled escape importunities anxious consult . =Nessus= (Nesʹsus). name Centaur destroyed Hercules insulting wife Deianira. Nessus'blood-smeared robe proved fatal Hercules. =Nestor= (Nesʹtor). grandson Neptune, father Neleus, mother Chloris. Homer makes greatest Greek heroes. present famous battle Lapithae Centaurs, took leading part Trojan war. "... 'Nestor Instructed antiquary times, must, , cannot wise." Shakespeare. =Nicephorus= (Nicephʹorus). name Jupiter, meaning bearer victory. =Nidhogg= (Nidʹhogg). Scandinavian mythology dragon dwells Nastrond. =Niflheim= (Niflʹheim). Scandinavian hell. supposed consist vast regions ice beneath North Pole, darkness reigns eternally. See Nastrond. =Night=, see Nox. =Nightingale=, see Philomela. =Nightmare=, see Incubus. =Nilus= (Niʹlus), king Thebes, gave name Nile, great Egyptian river. =, =, see Muses. =Niobe= (Niʹobe) daughter Tantalus, personification grief. husband Amphion sons daughters. orders Latona father sons killed Apollo, daughters (except Chloris) Diana. Niobe, overwhelmed grief, escaped trouble turned stone. =Nomius= (ʹmius). law-giver; names Apollo. title also given Mercury part took inventing beneficent laws. =Norns.= Scandinavian goddesses, wove woof human destiny. witches Shakespeare'"Macbeth" origin Scandinavian Norns. =Notus= (ʹtus). Another name Auster, south wind. =Nox= daughter Chaos, sister Erebus Mors. personified night, mother Nemesis Fates. =Nundina= (Nundiʹna). goddess took charge children days old--day (_Nona dies_) Romans named children. =Nuptialis= (Nuptiaʹlis). title Juno. goddess invoked name gall victim taken thrown behind altar, signifying gall (bitterness) anger married people. =Nuriel= (Nuʹriel). Hebrew mythology god hailstorms. =Nyctelius= (Nycteʹlius). name given Bacchus, festivals celebrated torchlight. =Nymphs.= general name class inferior female deities attendants gods. presided springs, fountains, wells, woods, sea. spoken land-nymphs Naiads, sea-nymphs Nereids, though former associated also fountains rivers. Dryads forest-nymphs, Hamadryads nymphs lived among oak-trees--oak always specially venerated ancients. mountain-nymphs called Oreads. "flower-inwoven tresses torn, nymphs twilight shade tangled thickets mourn." Milton. =Nysae= (Nyʹsae). names nymphs Bacchus nursed. See Dionysius. =Nysaeus= (Nyʹsaeus). name Bacchus, worshiped Nysa, town Aethiopia. =Nysus= (Nyʹsus). king Megara invisible virtue particular lock hair. lock daughter Scylla cut , betrayed father enemies. changed lark, king hawk, still pursues daughter, intending punish treachery. =Oannes= (Oanʹnes). Eastern (Babylonian) god, represented monster, half-man, half-fish. said taught men use letters day-time, night retired depth ocean. =Oath=, see Lapis. =Obambou= (Obamʹbou). devil African mythology. =Ocean=, see Neptune. =Oceanides= (Oceanʹides). Sea-nymphs, daughters Oceanus Tethys. numbers variously estimated different poets; saying many 3,000, others say sixteen. principal mentioned respective names, Amphitrite, Doris, Metis, etc. =Oceanus= (Oceʹanus), son Coelus Terra, husband Tethys. Several mythological rivers called sons, Alpheus, Peneu