oned Theseus. =Onuva= (Onuʹva). Venus ancient Gauls. =Opalia= (Opaʹlia). Roman festivals honor Ops, held 14th calends January. =Opiate-rod=, see Caduceus. "Eyes ... wakeful drowse, Charmed Arcadian pipe--pastoral reed Hermes opiate-rod." Milton. =Ops.= Mother gods, daughter Coelus Terra. known several names Bona Dea, Rhea, Cybele, Magna Mater, Proserpine, Tellus, Thya; occasionally spoken Juno Minerva. personified labor, represented comely matron, distributing gifts right hand, holding left hand loaf bread. festival 14th day January calends. =Oracles=, see Themis. =Oraea= (Oraeʹ). Certain sacrifices offered goddesses seasons invoke fair weather ripening fruits earth. =Orbona= (Orboʹna). Roman goddess children, invoked mothers lost danger losing offspring. =Orchards=, see Feronia. =Oreades= (Oʹreades) mountain nymphs, attendants Diana. =Orgies.= Drunken revels. riotous feasts Bacchus designated. =Orion= (Oriʹ). handsome hunter, great stature, blinded Oenopion grievous wrong done Merope, therefore expelled Chios. sound Cyclops' hammers led abode Vulcan, gave guide. consulted oracle, sight restored, Longfellow says, fixing "blank eyes upon sun." afterward slain Diana placed amongst stars, constellation splendid. =Orithyia= (Oriʹthyʹia). daughter Erechtheus, whose lover, Boreas, carried wandering river Ilissus. children Zetus Calais, winged warriors accompanied Argonauts. =Ormuzd= (ʹmuzd). Persian mythology creator things. =Oros= (Oʹros). Egyptian Apollo. =Orphans=, see Orbona. =Orpheus= (ʹpheus) son Apollo Muse Calliope. married Eurydice; stung serpent, died. Orpheus went Hades claim , played sweetly lute Pluto allowed Eurydice return earth Orpheus, condition look behind reached terrestrial regions. Orpheus, however, anxiety see following , looked round, Eurydice disappeared sight, instantly forever. "Orpheus' lute strung poets' sinews." Shakespeare. =Osiris= (Osiʹris). Egyptian god sun, source warmth, life, fruitfulness; worshiped form sacred bull, named Apis. "... appeared crew , names old renown, Osiris, Isis, Orus, train, monstrous shapes sorceries abused Fanatic Egypt priests seek wandering gods, disguised brutish forms Rather human." Milton. =Ossa= (Osʹsa). mountains Thessaly (residence centaurs) giants piled top Mount Pelion enable ascend heaven attack gods. =Ox=, see Apis. =Owl=, see Aesculapius Itys. =Pactolus= (Pactoʹlus). river Lydia Midas washed order Bacchus, sands turned gold. =Paean= (Paeʹ). name given Apollo, _paean_, hymn sung honor killed serpent Python. Paeans solemn songs, praying either averting evil rescue, giving thanks help vouchsafed. "hymns divine joyous banquet ends, Paeans lengthened till sun descends." Pope. =Palaemon= (Palaeʹmon), Melicerta, sea-god, son Athamas Ino. =Pales= (Paʹles). goddess shepherds sheepfolds protectress flocks; festivals called Romans Palilia. "Pomona loves orchard, Liber loves wine, Pales loves straw-built shed, Warm breath kine." Macaulay. "Great Pales help, pastoral rites sing, humble duty mentioning thing." Pope. =Palladium= (Pallaʹdium). famous statue goddess Pallas (Minerva). sitting spear right hand, left distaff spindle. Various accounts given origin statue. writers say fell skies. supposed preservation statue preservation Troy; Trojan War Greeks greatly encouraged became possessors . =Pallas= (Palʹlas), Minerva. name given Minerva destroyed famous giant named Pallas. Greeks called goddess wisdom Pallas Athene. See Minerva. "Apollo, Pallas, Jove, Mercury, Inspire treason find." Shakespeare. [Illustration: Iris _See page 73_] =Pan.= Arcadian god shepherds, huntsmen, country folk, chief inferior deities, usually considered son Mercury Penelope. birth metamorphosed mythical form find depicted, namely, horned, long-eared man, lower half body like goat. generally seen playing pipe made reeds various lengths, invented , produce music charmed even gods. Pan-pipes, _Syrinx_. Pan'terrific appearance frightened Gauls invaded Greece ran away though pursued ; word _panic_ said derived episode. Fauns, greatly resembled Pan, attendants. "Piping reeds shepherds go, fear ambush, suspect foe." Pope. =Pandora= (Pandoʹra), according Hesiod, first mortal female. Vulcan made clay, gave life. Venus gave beauty; art captivating bestowed upon Graces. taught singing Apollo, Mercury taught oratory. Jupiter gave box, famous "Pandora'Box," told give husband, Epimetheus, brother Prometheus. soon opened issued numberless diseases evils soon spread world, moment afflicted human race. said Hope alone remained box. Pandora means "-gifted." "lovely Pandora, gods Endowed gifts." Milton. =Pantheon= (Pantheʹ) (lit. "-divine place"). temple gods, built Agrippa Rome, reign Augustus (B.C. 27). 144 feet diameter, 144 feet high; built Corinthian style architecture, mostly marble; walls covered engraved brass silver. magnificence induced Pliny give rank among wonders world. =Paphia= (Paʹphia), name Venus. =Papremis= (Papʹremis). Egyptian Mars. =Parcae, = (Parʹcae), goddesses presided destiny human beings. also called Fates, number, Atropos, Clotho, Lachesis. See Fates. =Paris= (Parʹ), son Priam, king Troy, mother Hecuba. predicted cause destruction Troy, father therefore ordered strangled soon born; slave entrusted mission took child Mount Ida, left . shepherds, however, found infant took care . lived among till grown man'estate, married Oenone, nymph Ida. famous nuptial feast Peleus Thetis, Discordia, invited, attended secretly; assembled, threw among goddesses golden apple, inscribed "fairest take ." occasioned great contention, thought fairest. Ultimately, contestants reduced , Juno, Pallas (Minerva), Venus; Jove make agree, decided Paris umpire. sent , goddesses courted favor offering sorts bribes. Juno offered power, Pallas wisdom, Venus promised beautiful woman world. Paris gave golden apple Venus. Soon episode Priam owned Paris son, sent Greece fetch Helen, renowned beautiful woman world. wife Menelaus, king Sparta; absence Paris carried Helen away Troy, gave rise celebrated war Greeks Trojans, ended destruction Troy. Paris among 676,000 Trojans fell siege. =Parnassides= (Parnasʹsides), name common Muses, Mount Parnassus. =Parnassus= (Parnasʹsus). mountain Muses Phocis, sacred Apollo Bacchus. slept mountain became poet. named sons Bacchus. =Parthenon= (Parʹthenon). temple Minerva (Pallas) Acropolis Athens. destroyed Persians, rebuilt Pericles. =Parthenos= (Parʹthenos) name Juno, also Minerva. See Pallas. =Pasiphae= (Pasiphʹae) reputed mother Minotaur killed Theseus. said daughter Sol Perseis, husband Minos, king Crete. =Pasithea= (Pasithʹea). Sometimes __ Graces spoken ; , name fourth Pasithea. Also called Aglaia. =Pavan= (Pavʹ), Hindoo god winds. =Peace=, see Concordia. =Peacock=, see Argus. =Pegasus= (Pegʹasus). famous winged horse said sprung blood Medusa head cut Perseus. abode Mount Helicon, , striking ground hoof, caused water spring forth, formed fountain afterward called Hippocrene. "spurs faded Pegasus apace." Byron. "Thy stumbling founder'd jade trot high Pegasus fly." Earl Dorset. "turn wind fiery Pegasus, witch world noble horsemanship." Shakespeare. =Peleus= (Peʹleus). king Thessaly, married Thetis, Nereides. said mortal married immortal. =Pelias= (Peʹlias). son Neptune Tyro. usurped throne Cretheus, Jason persuaded relinquish take command Argonautic expedition. return Jason, Medea, sorceress, undertook restore Pelias youth, required body first cut put caldron boiling water. done, Medea refused fulfil promise. Pelias daughters, called Peliades. =Pelias= (Peʹlias) name spear Achilles, large none wield hero . =Pelion= (Peʹlion). well-wooded mountain, famous wars giants gods, abode Centaurs, expelled Lapithae. See Ossa, mount, giants piled upon Pelion, enable scale heavens. "gods challenge, affect skies, Heaved Olympus tottering Ossa stood; Ossa, Pelion nods wood." Pope. =Pelops= (Peʹlops), son Tantalus, king Phrygia. father killed , served eaten feast given gods, , found father Pelops done, restored son life, afterward became husband Hippodamia. =Penates= (Penaʹtes). Roman domestic gods. hearth house altar. See Lares. =Perpetual Punishment=, see Sisyphus. =Persephone= (Persephʹ). Greek name Proserpine. =Perseus= (Perʹseus) son Jupiter Danae, daughter Acrisius. first famous exploit Gorgon, Medusa. assisted enterprise Pluto, lent helmet make invisible. Pallas lent shield, Mercury supplied wings. made speedy conquest Gorgons, cut Medusa'head, flew air, blood sprang winged horse Pegasus. flew along saw Andromeda chained rock, sea-monster ready devour . killed monster, married Andromeda. got back, showed Gorgon'head King Polydectes, monarch immediately turned stone. "Daedalian waxen pinions stray, wafted Perseus way." F. Lewis. =Persuasion=, goddess , see Pitho. =Phaeton= (Phaʹeton). son Sol, , according many mythologists, Phoebus Clymene. Anxious display skill horsemanship, allowed drive chariot sun day. horses soon found incapacity charioteer, became unmanageable, overturned chariot. great fear injury heaven earth, Jove, stop destruction, killed Phaeton thunderbolt. "Phaeton, lofty hopes possessed, burning seat youthful vigor pressed." "breathless Phaeton, flaming hair, Shot chariot like falling star summer'evening top heaven drops , seems least drop." Addison. =Phaon= (Phaʹ). boatman Mitylene, Lesbos, received Venus box ointment, , anointed , grew beautiful Sappho became enamored ; ointment used Phaon returned former condition, Sappho, despair, drowned . =Pheasant=, see Itys. =Philoctetes= (Philoctʹetes) son Poeas, companions Jason Argonautic expedition. present death Hercules, received poisoned arrows dipped blood Hydra. arrows, oracle declared, necessary used destruction Troy, Philoctetes persuaded Ulysses go assist siege. appears used weapons great dexterity wonderful effect, Paris among heroes killed. story Philoctetes dramatized Greek tragedians Aeschylus, Euripides, Sophocles. =Philomela= (Philomeʹla) daughter Pandion, king Athens, transformed nightingale. sister Procne, married Tereus, King Thrace. latter offered violence Philomela, sister, Procne, came rescue, punish husband slew son Itylus, feast Philomela threw Itylus'head banquet table. "Forth like fury Philomela flew, face head Itys threw." Pope. "thou, melodious Philomel, thy plaintive story tell." Sir Thomas Lyttleton. =Phlegethon= (Phlegʹethon). river fire infernal regions. picture desolation, nothing grow parched withered banks. Also called Pyriphlegethon. "... Infernal rivers ... ... Fierce Phlegethon, Whose waves torrent fire inflame rage." Milton. =Phlegon= (Phleʹgon) (burning), chariot horses Sol. =Phlegyas= (Phleʹgyas). Son Mars father Ixion Coronis. impiety desecrating plundering temple Apollo Delphi, sent Hades, made sit huge stone suspended head, ready dropped moment. =Phoebus= (Phoeʹbus). name Apollo, signifying light life. "Gallop apace, fiery-footed steeds, Toward Phoebus' lodging." Shakespeare. =Phorcus= (Phorʹcus), =Porcys=. son Neptune, father Gorgons. Oceanus. =Phryxus= (Phryxʹ), see Golden Fleece. =Picumnus= (Picumʹnus). rural divinity, presided manuring lands, also called Sterentius. =Picus= (Piʹcus). son Saturn, father Faunus, turned woodpecker Circe, whose love requited. =Pierides= (Pierʹides). name Muses, derived Pieria, fountain Thessaly, near Mount Olympus, supposed born. Also, daughters Pierus, king Macedonia, settled Boeotia. challenged Muses sing, changed magpies. =Pietas= (Pieʹtas). Roman goddess domestic affection. =Pillar=, see Calpe. =Pilumnus= (Pilumʹnus). rural divinity presided corn ground. Rome hence called god bakers. =Pine-Tree=, see Atys. =Pirithous= (Pirithʹous). son Ixion great friend Theseus, king Athens. marriage Pirithous Hippodamia became famous quarrel drunken Centaurs Lapithae, , help Theseus, Pirithous, Hercules, attacked overcame Centaurs, many killed, remainder took flight. =Pitho= (Piʹtho), goddess Persuasion, daughter Mercury Venus. sometimes referred name Suada. =Plants=, see Demogorgon. =Pleasure=, see Rembha. =Pleiades, = (