l; first moment vital breath, last hour unrepenting death." Dryden. =Rhamnusia= (Rhamnuʹsia). name Nemesis, Rhamnus, town Attica, temple statue, made stone cubits high. =Rhea= (Rheʹ). Greek name Cybele. daughter Uranus Gaea, called Mother gods. =Rhetoric=, see Calliope, also Polyhymnia. =Riches=, see Plutus. =Riddle=, see Sphinx. =Rimmon= (Rimʹmon). Phrygian god Milton says-- "... Rimmon, whose delightful seat fair Damascus, fertile banks Abana Pharpar, lucid streams." =Riot=, see Saturnalia. =River Fire=, see Phlegethon. =Roads=, see Vialis. =Robber=, see Cacus, Coeculus. =Romulus= (Romʹulus). traditional founder Rome. son Mars Ilia, twin brother Remus. infants thrown Tiber, miraculously saved suckled -wolf, till found Faustulus, shepherd, brought . Remus killed quarrel brother, Romulus became first King Rome. =Rumia Dea= (RumiʹDea). Roman goddess babes arms. =Rumina= (Ruʹmina). Roman pastoral deities, protected suckling cattle. =Runcina= (Runciʹna). goddess weeding cleansing ground. =Sacrifices= ceremonious offerings made gods. every deity distinct victim allotted, greatest care always taken selection . Anything way blemished considered insult god. time sacrifice people called together heralds led procession musicians. priest, clothed white, crowned wreath made leaves tree sacred particular god sacrifice offered. victim horns gilt, adorned chaplet similar priest, decorated bright-colored ribbons. priest said, "?" spectators replied, "Many good people." "Begone ye profane," said priest; began prayer addressed gods. sacrifice begun putting corn, frankincense, flour, salt, cakes, fruit head victim. called Immolation. priest took cup wine, tasted , handed bystanders taste also; poured horns victim, saturated hairs pulled put fire burning altar. , turning east, priest drew knife crooked line along back beast head tail, told assistants kill animal. done directly, entrails victim taken carefully examined Haruspices find prognosticated. carcase divided, thighs, covered fat, put fire, rest animal cut , cooked, eaten. feast celebrated dancing, music, hymns, praise god whose honor sacrifice made. great occasions many hundred bullocks offered time; said Pythagoras made offering found demonstration forty-seventh proposition book Euclid. =Saga= (Saʹga). Scandinavian goddess history. word means _saw_ saying; hence Sagas, embody Scandinavian legends, heroic mythical traditions. =Sagittarius= (Sagittaʹrius), see Chiron. =Sails=, see Daedalus. =Salamanders= (Salʹamanʹders). genii , according Plato, lived fire. "spirits fiery termagants flame, Mount take Salamander'name." Pope. =Salatia= (Salaʹtia), Salacia, Roman goddess salt water. See Amphitrite. =Salii= (Salʹii). priests Mars charge sacred shields. =Salmoneus= (Salmoʹneus). king Elis , trying imitate Jupiter'thunders, sent god straight infernal regions. =Salus= (Saʹlus). Roman goddess health. =Sappho= (Sapʹpho), celebrated poetess, native Lesbos, flourished seventh century B.C. connection goddesses time Greeks called "tenth Muse." =Sarcasm=, see Momus. =Saron= (Saʹron), sea-god. =Sarpedon= (Sarpeʹ), son Jupiter Europa. accompanied Glaucus, latter set assist Priam Greeks Trojan War. slain Patroclus. =Saturn= (Satʹurn), king Universe, father Jupiter, Neptune, Pluto. gods quarreled amongst division father'kingdom, ended Jupiter heaven earth, Neptune sea, Pluto infernal regions. =Saturnalia= (Saturnaʹlia). Festivals held honor Saturn 16th 18th December. Principally famous riotous disorder generally attended . =Saturnius= (Saturʹnius). name given Jupiter, Neptune, Pluto, sons Saturn. =Satyavrata= (Satyaʹvraʹta). Hindoo god law. Menu. =Satyrs= (Satʹyrs). Spirits woodland, half men, half goats, fond wine women. attendants Dionysus, similar respects fauns attended Pan. See Silenus. "satyrs woodland sort. . . . . . . asses' hoofs, great goggle eyes, double chins monstrous size." Yalden. =Scylla= (Scylʹla). beautiful nymph excited jealousy Neptune'wife, Amphitrite, changed goddess frightful sea-mons